'''外百老汇'''（{{Lang-en|Off-Broadway}}）指的是位于[[美国|美国]][[纽约市|纽约市]]的[[座位数|座位数]]在100到499座之间的[[剧场|剧场]]；其座位数比[[百老汇|百老汇]]少但比[[外外百老汇|外外百老汇]]多，后者的座位数通常少于100座。

“外百老汇作品”则指的是在外百老汇上演并遵守相关[[工会|工会]]和其他协议规定的[[戏曲剧本|戏剧]]、[[音乐剧|音乐剧]]及{{Link-en|活报剧|Revue}}等作品。<ref name="ATPAM">{{cite web |title=Minimum Basic Agreement Between ATPAM and the League of Off-broadway Theatres and Producers, Inc. |url=http://www.offbroadway.org/OB_MBA_2001a.pdf |publisher=The Association of Theatrical Press Agents and Managers |accessdate=2022-06-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040611091424/http://www.offbroadway.org/OB_MBA_2001a.pdf |archivedate=2004-05-11 |language=en |date=2001-07-01}}</ref> 一些在外百老汇首演的作品随后会交由百老汇制作。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Lee Seymour |title=Off Broadway Theater Isn't Dying - It's Evolving. And It's More Profitable Than Ever |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/leeseymour/2018/01/17/off-broadway-theater-isnt-dying-its-evolving-and-its-more-profitable-than-ever/ |publisher=[[福布斯|福布斯]] |accessdate=2022-06-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180117181738/https://www.forbes.com/sites/leeseymour/2018/01/17/off-broadway-theater-isnt-dying-its-evolving-and-its-more-profitable-than-ever/ |archivedate=2018-01-17 |language=en |date=2018-01-17}}</ref>

== 发展历史 ==
“外百老汇”最初指的是位于[[美国|美国]][[纽约市|纽约市]][[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]]一条与[[紐約劇場區|剧场区]][[百老匯|百老汇大道]]相交道路上的剧场及在这里制作演出的戏剧作品；百老汇大道被认为是纽约戏剧产业的中心。但随后“外百老汇”被外百老汇剧场与制作人联盟（{{lang|en|League of Off-Broadway Theatres and Producers}}）定义为位于曼哈顿且[[座位数|座位数]]在100到499座之间的专业演出场地，以及在此场地上演并符合相关[[工会|工会]]及其他协议所规定的特定作品。<ref name="ATPAM" />

曾经，无论场地的大小，只要该场地位于“百老汇方框（{{lang|en|Broadway Box}}）”内就会被视为属于百老汇剧场而非外百老汇剧场。“百老汇方框”的范围东起[[第六大道|第六大道]]而西至[[第八大道|第八大道]]，南达第40街北抵{{Link-en|第54街 (曼哈顿)|54th Street (Manhattan)|第54街}}；这其中包括了[[时报广场|时报广场]]和西[[42街_(曼哈頓)|第42街]]。对“外百老汇”合同定义的改变使得满足于499座标准的剧场收益，因为百老汇戏剧公会对演员的最低薪资要求要比非百老汇戏剧公会要高。<ref>{{cite web |title=How To Tell Broadway From Off-Broadway From... |url=https://www.playbill.com/article/how-to-tell-broadway-from-off-broadway-from-com-110450 |publisher=Playbill |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |date=2019-01-13 |quote=The distinction generally has to do with theatre size (but not 100 percent of the time). Theatres with up to 99 seats generally are considered Off-Off-Broadway; 99-499 seats generally denote Off-Broadway; and 500 and larger generally denote Broadway. There are many exceptions, however, and some overlap. The real key is what sort of contract the production has. |archive-date=2019-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021180407/http://www.playbill.com/article/how-to-tell-broadway-from-off-broadway-from-com-110450 }}</ref> 而499座这个上限标准诞生于1974年1月的一次为期1天的[[罷工|罢工运动]]中。<ref>{{cite web |title=Fate and Fortune |url=https://www.actorsequity.org/timeline/timeline_1970.html |publisher={{Link-en|演员权益协会|Actors' Equity Association}} |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |quote=A one-day Off-Broadway strike ends with no performances missed. Equity agrees to increase the number of seats a theatre may have for an Off-Broadway production from 299 to 499. Don Grody writes, "we have opened the door to the possibility of a commercially viable Off-Broadway." |archive-date=2021-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211217203647/https://www.actorsequity.org/timeline/timeline_1970.html }}</ref> 位于百老汇方框内的非百老汇剧场案例有{{Link-en|圆环剧院公司|Roundabout Theatre Company|劳拉·派尔剧院}}和{{Link-en|剧院中心|The Theater Center}}。

外百老汇运动始于1950年代，这是对百老汇商业主义的抵制，同时为那些雇佣许多未来百老汇表演艺术家的作品提供更廉价的演出场所。1952年，由[[田纳西·威廉斯|田纳西·威廉斯]]所制作的《{{Link-en|夏日烟云|Summer and Smoke}}》在{{Link-en|中环广场剧院|Circle in the Square Theatre}}上演，这被认为是外百老汇运动在早期的一个成功案例。<ref>{{cite web |title=Circle in the Square papers |url=https://archives.nypl.org/the/21843#access_use |publisher=The New York Public Library |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |archive-date=2021-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210713200321/http://archives.nypl.org/the/21843#access_use }}</ref> 而根据戏剧历史学家肯·布鲁姆（{{lang|en|Ken Bloom}}）和弗兰克·弗拉斯特尼克（{{lang|en|Frank Vlastnik}}）的说法，外百老汇为“[[诗人|诗人]]、[[剧作家|剧作家]]、[[演员|演员]]、[[词曲作者|词曲作者]]和[[舞台设计师|舞台设计师]]们提供了一个新的出路，……第一部伟大的外百老汇作品是《[[三文钱的歌剧|三文钱的歌剧]]》在1954年的复演”，这证明了外百老汇作品同样可以在财务上取得成功。<ref name="Bloom">{{cite book |author1=Ken Bloom |author2=Frank Vlastnik |coauthors=Jerry Orbach (修订) |title=Broadway Musicals: The 101 Greatest Shows of All Time |date=2008 |publisher=Black Dog & Leventhal |isbn=9781579123130 |page=94 |edition=Revised Version |language=en}}</ref> 位于[[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]][[第九大道|第九大道]]与[[第十大道|第十大道]]之间的西[[42街_(曼哈頓)|第42街]]部分路段也被称为“{{Link-en|剧场路 (纽约市)|Theatre Row (New York City)|剧场路}}”，这里集中了大量外百老汇及[[外外百老汇|外外百老汇]]剧场。这里于1970年代进行开发，并在2002年完成现代化改造。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jesse McKinley |title=Upscale March Of Theater Row; A Centerpiece of Redevelopment |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/21/theater/upscale-march-of-theater-row-a-centerpiece-of-redevelopment.html |publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]] |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |date=2002-11-21 |archive-date=2022-06-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220601074112/https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/21/theater/upscale-march-of-theater-row-a-centerpiece-of-redevelopment.html }}</ref>

许多外百老汇作品在上演一段时间后也会在百老汇上演，这其中包括不少后来在百老汇获得成功的[[音乐剧|音乐剧]]。例如：《[[毛髮_(音樂劇)|毛发]]》、《{{Link-en|福音摇滚|Godspell}}》、《{{Link-en|恐怖小店 (音乐剧)|Little Shop of Horrors (musical)|恐怖小店}}》、《{{Link-en|星期天与乔治同游公园|Sunday in the Park with George}}》、《[[吉屋出租|吉屋出租]]》、《{{Link-en|灰色花园 (音乐剧)|Grey Gardens (musical)|灰色花园}}》、《{{Link-en|尿镇|Urinetown}}》、《[[Q大道|Q大道]]》、《{{Link-en|第25届布南区串字大赛|The 25th Annual Putnam County Spelling Bee}}》、《{{Link-en|摇滚年代 (音乐剧)|Rock of Ages (musical)|摇滚年代}}》、《{{Link-en|身在高地|In the Heights}}》、《{{Link-en|春之苏醒 (音乐剧)|Spring Awakening (musical)|春之苏醒}}》、《{{Link-en|近乎正常|Next to Normal}}》、《{{Link-en|摇滚芭比 (音乐剧)|Hedwig and the Angry Inch (musical)|摇滚芭比}}》、《{{Link-en|娱乐之家 (音乐剧)|Fun Home (musical)|娱乐之家}}》、《[[漢密爾頓_(音樂劇)|汉密尔顿]]》、《[[致埃文·汉森|致埃文·汉森]]》和《{{Link-en|冥界 (音乐剧)|Hadestown|冥界}}》。<ref>{{cite web |title=10 Reasons to Go Off-broadway |url=http://offbroadway.com/about.php |publisher=League of Off-Broadway Theatres and Producers |accessdate=2022-06-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130052411/http://offbroadway.com/about.php |archivedate=2017-01-30 |language=en}}</ref> 特别是《[[油脂_(音樂劇)|油脂]]》和《[[歌舞线上|歌舞线上]]》在迁演至百老汇依然火爆的现象促使其他制作人开始考虑在外百老汇首演他们的作品。<ref name="Bloom" /> 而从外百老汇迁演到百老汇的舞台剧则有《{{Link-en|怀疑：一则寓言|Doubt: A Parable}}》、《{{Link-en|吾亦吾妻|I Am My Own Wife}}》、《{{Link-en|纽约城外 (舞台剧)|Bridge and Tunnel (play)|纽约城外}}》、《{{Link-en|平常心 (舞台剧)|The Normal Heart|平常心}}》和《{{Link-en|海岸风雨|Coastal Disturbances}}》。但是也有《[[破铜烂铁乐队|破铜烂铁乐队]]》、《{{Link-en|蓝人乐团|Blue Man Group}}》、《{{Link-en|祭坛男孩|Altar Boyz}}》、《{{Link-en|完美犯罪 (舞台剧)|Perfect Crime (play)|完美犯罪}}》、《{{Link-en|禁忌百老汇|Forbidden Broadway}}》、《{{Link-en|修女的故事 (音乐剧)|Nunsense|修女的故事}}》、《{{Link-en|裸男歌唱 (音乐剧)|Naked Boys Singing!|裸男歌唱}}》、《{{Link-en|蝙蝠男孩：音乐剧|Bat Boy: The Musical}}》、《[[我爱你，你太完美了。所以，还是改变一下吧|我爱你，你太完美了。所以，还是改变一下吧]]》等作品在外百老汇上演多年，但却一直拒绝迁演到百老汇。《{{Link-en|梦幻爱程|The Fantasticks}}》是戏剧史上上演时间最长的作品，它的原版曾在外百老汇持续上演42年。<ref>{{cite web |title=The Fantasticks Bids Farewell, Jan. 13, After 42 Years on Sullivan Street |url=https://www.playbill.com/article/the-fantasticks-bids-farewell-jan-13-after-42-years-on-sullivan-street-com-103329 |publisher=Playbill |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |date=2002-01-23 |archive-date=2022-06-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220601083136/https://playbill.com/article/the-fantasticks-bids-farewell-jan-13-after-42-years-on-sullivan-street-com-103329 }}</ref> 而从2006年开始，该剧在外百老汇复演，开启了它又一段长期上演的历史。<ref>{{cite web |author1=David Gordon |title=After 56 Years, Tom Jones Isn't Finished With The Fantasticks |url=https://www.theatermania.com/california-theater/news/interview-tom-jones-the-fantasticks_78283.html |publisher=TheaterMania |accessdate=2022-06-01 |language=en |date=2016-09-09 |archive-date=2022-06-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220601083129/https://www.theatermania.com/california-theater/news/interview-tom-jones-the-fantasticks_78283.html }}</ref>

== 主要奖项 ==
外百老汇表演、演出人员和创作人员有资格参与{{Link-en|纽约戏剧评论人协会|New York Drama Critics' Circle|纽约戏剧评论人协会奖}}、{{Link-en|外围评论人协会奖|Outer Critics Circle Award}}、[[戏剧桌奖|戏剧桌奖]]、{{Link-en|奥比奖|Obie Award}}、{{Link-en|露西尔·洛特尔奖|Lucille Lortel Awards}}和{{Link-en|戏剧联盟奖|Drama League Award}}等奖项的评选。而虽然外百老汇表演无法参与[[托尼奖|托尼奖]]评选，但在1956年，[[罗特·莲娜|罗特·莲娜]]凭借外百老汇戏剧作品《[[三文钱的歌剧|三文钱的歌剧]]》而获得了{{Link-en|托尼奖最佳音乐剧女主角|Tony Award for Best Featured Actress in a Musical}}。<ref>{{cite web |title=Trivia |url=http://www.threepennyopera.org/histOffBway.php#trivia |publisher=The Threepenny Opera |accessdate=2022-06-01 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060722011504/http://www.threepennyopera.org/histOffBway.php#trivia |archivedate=2006-07-22 |language=en |quote=Despite playing off-Broadway, Threepenny took two Tony Awards in 1956: one for Lotte Lenya as Featured Actress and a special award for the show as a whole. Scott Merrill was nominated for Supporting Actor in a Musical, but lost out to Russ Brown of Damn Yankees.}}</ref>

